phase-review: feat/hy2-live-users — Ф2 one-command installer (install.sh) v1 [core]
change: replaced legacy s-ui systemd/release-tarball install.sh with a Docker-based
  one-command installer. Flow: install Docker (get.docker.com, idempotent) -> resolve
  image (GHCR pull -> local hypanel:dev -> build-from-source fallback) -> run container
  (persist /opt/hypanel/{db,cert}, ports 2095/2096/80/443) -> generate RANDOM admin
  password + obscure panel path (./hypanel admin / setting) -> SSH-safe UFW (allow 22
  FIRST + nohup watchdog auto-disabling ufw in 300s unless cancelled = anti-lockout) ->
  print access summary. Idempotent (skips reconfig if /opt/hypanel/.access exists).
review: SELF-REVIEW + LIVE END-TO-END TEST on dev VPS 201.51.25.203 (the authoritative
  test for a shell installer). security review skipped per standing user rule. Full
  parallel agent review deferred to iteration 2 (before the public push).
bug found+fixed during test: `set -o pipefail` + `rand(){ tr </dev/urandom | head -c N }`
  -> head closes pipe -> tr SIGPIPE -> pipefail+errexit silently aborted the script at
  the credential step. Fixed: dropped pipefail (set -eu) + `|| true` on rand. Also
  public_ip now forces IPv4 (curl -4) — api64 had returned an unbracketed IPv6.
verification (VPS, detached run): full log reached summary; container Up; ufw ACTIVE
  with SSH(22) allowed and MY session survived enable; random creds+path applied;
  EXTERNAL curl http://201.51.25.203:2095/<randompath>/ = HTTP 307 (panel serves),
  old /app/ = 404 (path changed), sub 2096 responds. NOT pushed yet (local commit).
remaining (iteration 2): GHCR publish Action (fast pull instead of slow/ OOM-risky
  build-from-source on small VPS) + zero-DNS TLS (<ip>.sslip.io + Let's Encrypt) ->
  then parallel code-review + push + final `bash <(curl ...)` one-command test.
